 <text>
  <front>
   <head>THE Expostulation.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">HOw long, great God, a  here,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Must I these hated marks of bondage wear?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How long shall these  controul</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The willing flights of my impatient Soul?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How long shall her</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="14">Be strain'd through an infectious screen of gross, corrupted sence?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When shall I leave this  of clay;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And to a brighter mansion wing away?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">There's nothing here my thoughts to entertain,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10" />
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Sun and Stars observe their wonted round,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="14">The streams their former courses keep:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The same curst acts of  o're,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The same wild hopes and wishes as before;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Do men for this so fondly life caress,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">(That airy huss of splendid emptiness?)</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Unthinking sots: kind Heaven let me be gone,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="14">I'm tyr'd, I'm sick of this</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
